records.addlTxt:
Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.

Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction (HOC) with credit for 62 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work, counseling, and school.  

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
*  Pay only the MANDATORY cost, due to the Defendant is indigent,  which includes the DNA fee out of bail on deposit, if any, with the balance due during the period of probation. Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  MAINTAIN full time / part time employment and or schooling.
*  Obtain a GED/HSED/Diploma.
*  Restitution set at ZERO.
*  No contact and not to be in possession of ANY animal for a period of 5 Years.
*  No contact with the victim Tori A.
*  Defendant required to provide a biological specimen (DNA) to the State Crime Lab for testing.
*  Participate in a Cognitive Thinking Program, and any other programming deemed appropriate by the Department and or agent.
